{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-classic-show-tsx","path":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-201-to-300/problem-265-binary-circles","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"block":"project-euler-problems-201-to-300","demoType":null,"title":"Vežba 265: Binarni kola","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Brojevi $2^N$ za binary mogu se postaviti u kolo da mala sekvenca brojeva $N$ za rotiranje sata bude sve različita.</p>\n<p>Za $N = 3$, dva rasporeda takvih ciklusa su mogući, bez uzimanja u obzir cikluse:</p>\n<img alt=\"two circular arrangements for N = 3\" src=\"https://cdn.freecodecamp.org/curriculum/project-euler/binary-circles.gif\" style=\"background-color: white; padding: 10px; display: block; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; margin-bottom: 1.2rem;\">\n<p>U prvom redosledu, kratka sekvenca od niza sa 3 bitova, u smeru kretanja po satu, je: 000, 001, 010, 101, 011, 111, 110 i 100.</p>\n<p>Svaki raspored kruga može se predstaviti brojem spajanjem binarnih brojeva počevši od sekvence svih nula kao najviši bit i nastavljajući u smeru zapivlja. Dva rasporeda za $N = 3$ su tako predstavljena sa 23 i 29:</p>\n<p>$${00010111}_2 = 23\\\\\n{00011101}_2 = 29$$</p>\n<p>Ako $S(N)$ je zbir jedinstvenih reprezentacija broja, možemo videti da $S(3) = 23 + 29 = 52$.</p>\n<p>Pronađi $S(5)$.</p>\n</section>","id":"5900f4761000cf542c50ff88","hasEditableBoundaries":false,"instructions":"","notes":null,"challengeType":1,"helpCategory":"Euler","videoUrl":null,"superBlock":"project-euler","translationPending":false,"forumTopicId":301914,"hooks":null,"fields":{"slug":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-201-to-300/problem-265-binary-circles"},"required":[],"usesMultifileEditor":false,"challengeFiles":[{"fileKey":"scriptjs","ext":"js","name":"script","contents":"function binaryCircles() {\n\n  return true;\n}\n\nbinaryCircles();","head":null,"tail":null,"editableRegionBoundaries":[],"history":["script.js"]}],"saveSubmissionToDB":null,"tests":[{"text":"<p><code>binaryCircles()</code> bi trebalo da vrati <code>209110240768</code>.</p>","testString":"assert.strictEqual(binaryCircles(), 209110240768);"}]}}},"pageContext":{"challengeMeta":{"blockHashSlug":"/learn/project-euler/#project-euler-problems-201-to-300","dashedName":"problem-265-binary-circles","certification":"project-euler","disableLoopProtectTests":true,"disableLoopProtectPreview":false,"superBlock":"project-euler","chapter":null,"module":null,"block":"project-euler-problems-201-to-300","isFirstStep":false,"template":null,"required":[],"isLastChallengeInBlock":false,"nextChallengePath":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-201-to-300/problem-266-pseudo-square-root","prevChallengePath":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-201-to-300/problem-264-triangle-centres","id":"5900f4761000cf542c50ff88","saveSubmissionToDB":null},"projectPreview":{"challengeData":{"challengeType":1,"challengeFiles":[{"name":"script","ext":"js","contents":"// solution required","history":["script.js"],"fileKey":"scriptjs"}]}},"id":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-201-to-300/problem-265-binary-circles"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3858520367"],"slicesMap":{}}